Okay. You have found yourself, either voluntarily or forced by circumstances, to teach your course online. 
It is our hope that the resources here will be a start for you to learn a little more. If you have specific questions, or want to learn more, please contact the Office of Digital Learning at 920-262-7500x6516 and we would love to talk to you more. We are here to help you and your students.
District teachers wishing to utilize our resources to get through the COVID-19 may choose between several options.
Current Resources
All Levels
Canvas - Our centrally supported learning management system (LMS) is called Canvas. You may be surprised to learn that by clicking on the provided link, as a WUSD teacher, you already have a learning shell setup for each of your assigned courses as defined in Skyward. Also, all of your students are already enrolled in the course. All you need to do is setup and publish your course and they may begin using it by going to the same link. Canvas is a great way to organize your class materials, online discussions (synchronous or asynchronous) assignments and even assessments related to your course.
SchoolsPLP - We have recently partnered with SchoolsPLP to provide a variety of online learning opportunities for our students. Curriculum providers include FYI Online Learning, eDynamic, Lincoln Learning, Comprehend, and Accelerate and students are able to choose from over 550 online course offerings PK through Grade 12. 


Grades 3 through 5
Odysseyware - Odysseyware is a great resource for providing content for our students in grades 3 through 12. It is a standards-based curriculum developed by Nationally Board Certified teachers and provides an opportunity for students to learn and demonstrate understanding of grade appropriate content standards.
Aleks - Through adaptive questioning and artificial intelligence, ALEKS accurately assesses a student's knowledge state and then delivers targeted instruction on the exact topics the student is most ready to learn.
Grades 6 through 12
Aleks - Through adaptive questioning and artificial intelligence, ALEKS accurately assesses a student's knowledge state and then delivers targeted instruction on the exact topics the student is most ready to learn.
Wisconsin eSchool Network (WeN) - WeN is a consortium of 28 schools around the State that share resources and provide learning opportunities for their students to learn in an online setting. WeN offers Standards Based courses that can be used in a blended or stand alone capacity.
As we work through the current crisis, we have the ability to offer over 300 already developed, age appropriate courses for our students. WeN has offered about 120 of these courses available to us for free through the end of June and designed them so that teachers need only enable the units/lessons/modules that they wish to use and students will be able to see them. We can have classes setup in a matter of a day or two (sometimes in hours) depending on your needs. This will prevent you from having to create your own course from scratch.
Odysseyware - Odysseyware is a great resource for providing content for our students in grades 3 through 12. It is a standards-based curriculum developed by Nationally Board Certified teachers and provides an opportunity for students to learn and demonstrate understanding of grade appropriate content standards.
Apex Learning - We are in the middle of a pilot program using Apex Learning. ApexVS has been in business for over 20 years and we have been using them since the mid-1990s. The curriculum is well scaffolded to support student learning and though this platform is not available for wide-spread rollout, we have a few seats open for teachers to pull from if desired.
